f, but can be an integral part of it. An extended introduction first sets out the theoretical basis for studies of ethical systems that are characterised by detailed rules. This is followed by a series of empirical studies of rule-oriented moral traditions in a comparative perspective.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSocial ethicsvCross-cultural studies. 0aSocial ethicsxHistory. 0aSocial ethics. 0aSocial normsvCross-cultural studies. 0aSocial normsxHistory. 0aSocial norms. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aMichel Foucault.  aThe Ten Commandments.  acasuistry.  acode of conduct.  aconscience.  ahalakha.  alegalism.  asharia.  atechnologies of the self.  avirtue ethics.1 aAl-Azem, Talal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Morgan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Morgan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCorran, Emily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorran, Emily, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDavis, Donald R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEmily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngram,  Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaidlaw, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLanglands, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLorenz, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinhardt, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchaeublin, Emanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook 